Subject: [sfraves] Solid Goldiggers Burlesque

Not my usual party post but a performance sure to be memorable!
Come get your spoken word fix and watch us dance....

Sex, Drugs, and Rock-n-Roll
A Night of Tits & Lit

Burlesque dancers and the best authors of transgressive literature
come together for a night of Sex, Drugs, and Rock-n-Roll.

September 9, 2006
Shotwell Studios  3252A 19th Street @ Shotwell
San Francisco
Doors 9:45PM Show 10:15PM
$3 - $5


FEATURE PERFORMERS:

Raina Bird, Tina Butcher, Tony DuShane, Lilycat, Carmelo Valone
& the Solid Golddiggers Burlesque Dancers

For more information contact: rainabird@hotmail.com
415-847-4026

BIOS:


Raina Bird was born in a cult run by a fat bald guy with 9 wives who
said he was the living incarnation of the divine. She now hates
hippies and religion with equal fervor. She is currently writing a
memoir about the experience. Her work has appeared in Morbid
Curiosity, Instant City and cherrybleeds. She is heavily tattooed,
very fond of her pet rat and leaves her house as little as possible

Tina Butcher - AKA Madison Young is a San Francisco based writer,
artist, and international bondage model. Tina's writing has been
published in such magazines as Girlfriends, On Our Backs, Bitch,
Herbivore, Skin Two, and in the anthology "Baby Remember My Name."
edited by Michelle Tea. Currently writes travel articles for Velvet
Park, and reviews for Skin Two, and is completing her memoir entitled
The Tail of a Bondage Model; Memoirs of Madison Young". Madison Young
has traveled the world working with some of the best bondage and
fetish photographers and rope artists in the business. Madison has
been published in over 100 web sites, numerous magazines including
Hustler's Taboo and Leg World, and score of bondage and fetish videos,
international bondage performances, and has started her own line of
bondage videos and websites including www.madisonBond.com and
www.Tied4Sex.com.

Tony DuShane- spends all his time writing, working on his radio show
Drinks with Tony, editing the literary 'zine Cherry Bleeds and bench
pressing women who weigh 165 or less.
His shoe size is 10 and his liver is strong.

Lilycat  Is a strong believer of supporting underground artists, loves
to write, is a fan of sex and rock-n-roll, knows a lot of people on
drugs, and likes to talk. You can find out about her at lilycat.com

Carmelo Valone- the troubled Carmelo Valone grew up surrounded by old
money and living dead residents of the suburbs of Connecticut. In the
early and dysfunctional 1990s he suffered a =8Cbreakdown=B9 and spent a
number of seasons in and out of McLean=B9s Psychiatric hospital. The
former home to numerous other troubled writers such as Silvia Plath,
Anne Sexton, and Susana Kaysen. He is a writer and is currently
working on a darkly humorous memoir about his young adult life in the
hospital called; "The Sex Life of a Lunatic" a search for love within
lunacy. He also has several screenplays and has acted and makes weird
electronic music. He loves to watch Prison Break and feeds ducks at
the Hollywood Forever cemetery.

BURLESQUE PERFORMANCES BY:

Solid Goldiggers Burlesque
A San Francisco based group founded in 2004 as a ladies night escape
from significant others. Consists of dancers Danielle Sipple Katie
Rose, Charlie Fisher, Bene, Melinda, and JoJo who all come from
various dance and theater backgrounds. Fusing the various dance styles
of ballet, theater, funk, and hip hop with traditional burlesque. The
Solid Goldiggers bring you performances like you've never seen that
accentuate all that is dance performance art with a twist of vintage
style and glamour.

Performing at various venues, such as Lingba Lounge, Element, Nickies,
Fashion events, and private events over the past year and a half.
Solid Goldiggers Burlesque continues to bring an element of excitement
and class to the world of dance entertainment while empowering
themselves, each other and their Audiences.

Subject: Re: [sfraves] The rave scene and what it's all about?

------=_Part_29018_10690540.1156956803210
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1; format=flowed
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Disposition: inline

Hi! Welcome to the list!

For me, parties (raves) are about electronic music and watching and feeling
peoples interaction to that music. Music is so emotional and nothing beats
being in a crowd of strangers all feeling something similar from a
particular sound. A DJ can control your night and bring you up and down OR
ruin it by having poor taste in record selection or sequencing and leaving
you in a low (luckily you can always go to another room or wait for the next
DJ to come on).

Music and parties have nothing to do with drugs, but like anything else in
life can be either enhanced or destroyed by it's use.

See you around!

Subject: [sfraves] FRESH: Escape from Planet Monday - US release :)





out 9/5  :)

System Recordings and HUMAN Imprint are proud to present 'Escape From
Planet
Monday' - the first full length artist album from UK drum and bass producer
extraordinaire, DJ Fresh. Featuring DJ Shadow, Apollo 440, Pet Shop Boys
and
the massive drum 'n' bass anthem "All That Jazz VIP", 'Escape From Planet
Monday' delivers everything you would expect from the man behind Bad
Company
UK.

'Escape From Planet Monday' is a rollercoaster ride through all of the
facets of DJ Fresh's imagination. DJ Fresh links Apollo 440 for "Nervous"
and the Pet Shop Boys for "Throw". He experiments with DJ Shadow for
"Closer" and brings in d'n'b sensations Pendulum for "Babylon Rising."
Couple that with all new mixes of club favorites "Submarines", "All That
Jazz" and "All Strung Out" and an album with many dimensions starts to
shape
up.

Catch DJ Fresh with Dieselboy on tour all Fall 2006 in support of 'Escape
>From Planet Monday'!

TRACKLISTING:
1. Nervous (Feat. Mary Byker of Apollo 440)
2. The Pink Panther
3. All That Jazz (Feat. MC Darrison)
4. Babylon Rising (Feat. Pendulum & Singing Fats)
5. Closer (Feat. DJ Shadow)
6. X Project Intro
7. X Project
8. The Immortal
9. Submarines (Domestic Cold War Edit)
10. Funk Academy Intro
11. Funk Academy
12. Looking Glass
13. All Strung Out (Thunder VIP)
14. Throw Intro
15. Throw (Feat. Neil Tennant)

+ "Nervous" VIDEO (Enhanced CD)

Subject: [sfraves] NRR: Terrorists "drive taxi cabs in the daytime and kill at night"

Go Montana!


Burns Says Terrorists Drive Taxis by Day
- By MATT GOURAS, Associated Press Writer
Thursday, August 31, 2006

(08-31) 07:00 PDT Belgrade, Mont. (AP) --

Republican Sen. Conrad Burns, whose recent comments have stirred
controversy, says the United States is up against a faceless enemy of
terrorists who "drive taxi cabs in the daytime and kill at night."

During a fundraiser Wednesday with first lady Laura Bush, the
three-term Montana senator talked about terrorism, tax cuts and the
money he has brought to his state. Burns is one of the more vulnerable
Senate incumbents, facing a tough challenge from Democrat Jon Tester.

He has drawn criticism in recent weeks for calling his house painter a
"nice little Guatemalan man" during a June speech. Burns, whose
re-election campaign is pressing for tighter immigration controls,
also suggested that the man might be an illegal immigrant. The
campaign later said the worker is legal.

Burns, 71, also had to apologize after confronting members of a
firefighting team at the Billings airport and telling them they had
done a "piss-poor job," according to a state report. In July, the
Hotshot crew had traveled 2,000 miles from Staunton, Va., to help dig
fire lines for about a week around a 143-square-mile wildfire east of
Billings.

At the campaign event with Bush, Burns talked about the war on
terrorism, saying a "faceless enemy" of terrorists "drive taxi cabs in
the daytime and kill at night."

Bush described Burns as a strong advocate for Montana farmers and families.

"In Washington, Senator Burns is a respected voice on the issues
facing rural communities in Montana and across the nation," Bush told
Burns supporters.

She also said Burns has been important in helping the president on key
initiatives, such as tax cuts, and has supported the troops fighting
in Iraq and the war on terror.

Our enemy is the Islamic fascists or Islamic extremists, terrorism is just a
form of fighting similar to guerrilla warfare. Anyone can be a terrorist
(Timmothy Mcvay), but the ones we need to concentrate this war on are the
Islamic fascist types (you know the ones that say they want to kill everyone
that isn't muslim). Obviously, this guy was just making a statement with his
shirt and was not a threat, just as all the loud UCSF students aren't a
threat. That was a nasty breach of his civil rights as an American citizen.
So how do we fight the IF's? Profile? Hope they all go to Iraq? What are we
to do as citizens that want to protect our country from attacks?

I don't think the hit and run rampage in SF requires
the brand of terrorism. Terrorism in definition is a
violent act presented by a group for some sort of
statement or cause. That hardly qualifies when the guy
stated he did it just because 'he wanted to'. I think
people generalize far too much when they call any act
by a muslim or someone of arab decent terrorism. That
word is thrown around far too much imo these days, and
is used to incite fear in the masses by the
government.

Well, how would you define war? There is a specific group of people out
there (Islamic extremists) that want to kill you and destroy your way of
life and they are actively looking for ways to do it.

 So that is not war? If they destroyed all the LSD and MDMA precursor
chemicals and your family would you still not be at war with them?

 I don't care if the "IF's" are black, white, yellow, red, or orange. Race
has nothing to do with it. If they happen to be of a certain race, well it
will just make them easier to find and profile, but that is about it.

Subject: [sfraves] BSP: LOVE INFUSION - Lovefest Afterparty - 4 rooms of sound

speaking of partying, this is one party that i'm really really excited about.

1)  it's our afterparty for Lovefest (yes, formely known as Love
Parade SF) and the party last year that Evil Breaks was a part of was
a fucking blast!

2)  we are working with 3 other crews that i have a huge amount of
respect for:  Opel, Tantra and the Ambient Mafia.  these are some
class act crews and very talented folks.  Opel and Tantra have thrown
some AMAZING events over the last few years.  the combination of all 4
crews is going to be fantastic.

3)  the lineup is HUGE!!!  Rennie Pilgrim, Hyper, General
Midi....these are gigantic names not just in the breaks world but in
the cross-genre global dance music world.  this really is one of the
biggest breaks lineups in SF for the entire year, no joke.

4)  we have SWAT sound and Viberation visuals in our room.  you know what's up.

5)  it's at SOMARTS bitchez!!!!

limited $20 presales are online at groovetickets:
http://www.groovetickets.com/ordersystem/Groove/eventviewqb.asp?AffilID=93&EventsID=24655&PGname=Opel

--

Opel in Association with
Evil Breaks, Tantra and the Ambient Mafia presents:

Love Infusion @ SOMArts
September 23, 2006
Presales start @ $20
9pm-6am

This is THE LoveFest Afterparty for 2006. Hands down. Here's why.....

Rennie Pilgrem (www.tcr.uk.com)
Hyper (Hope / Thrive, UK)
General Midi (TCR / Distinctive / Kilowatt / Boombox, UK)
Carbon Community (Sober Music / Bless, Dallas, TX)
J-Break (Afterdark Records, Florida)
+
Syd Gris (Opel / Opulent Temple)
Hoj (Opel / dhhoj.com)
Aaron Jae (Evil Breaks / XM Radio)
Melyss (Opel / Sister SF / Cheeky)
Bam (Evil Breaks / Invibe)
M.O.D. (Evil Breaks)
Athena (Evil Breaks)
Jay Vigor (StrategiK)

with TANTRA and the AMBIENT MAFIA

more BSP info to come shortly....

 MM: Were the Red Brigades terrifying? =20

ct, there are quite striking parallels between Islamic terrorism and the br=
igades. =20
 MM: What are the parallels? =20
 PS: The parallel is this culture of death. And the fact that in order to e=
nd up with this decision to kill and be killed, to commit suicide and take =
as many with you as you can, this logic is not one with the poor and suppre=
ssed of the world. It is an elite phenomenon. It has more to do with nihili=
sm than with any religion. To call it Islam is already misleading, because =
these guys are crazy politicians, ego-maniacs, disguised as religious fanat=
ics. It has nothing to do with religion. They're just criminals and fanatic=
s, total ego-maniacs. It's about egoism, solipsism, and not so much about r=
eligion. The war in Iraq has nothing to do with the fight against terrorism=
, it is a total deflection from this fight. The real danger is not these te=
rrorists, though they are dangerous, of course, but that millions of people=
 in the Arab world see them as heroes and identify with them. This is somet=
hing that you cannot heal with military campaigns. Here you must work with =
diplomacy,
 aid, politics. We have to ask ourselves: why do so many people identify wi=
th these idiots? =20
 MM: For Camus, "a nihilist does not believe what he sees". I visualize an =
economic war. =20
 PS: Yes, but we should not underestimate ideology. If people are now led b=
y Islamic fanatics, by priests, who tell them what to do, and if they do it=
 early enough, a boy of eight will start saying: "Yes, I want to be a suici=
de bomber, I want to be a suicide bomber. Allah is big in the world." It is=
 not only about economics. =20
 MM: Isn't culture a form of self-protection? =20
 PS: Absolutely. Culture is the most important thing we have to protect us =
against these forces. =20
 MM: Then why are governments withdrawing from culture? =20
 PS: This whole Bush thing is a culture of hypocrisy. This is all wrong, wh=
atever they say is just a lie. They say: "We want to care for the poor." Th=
ey act in the opposite direction. What is fascinating is that most of these=
 guys, who from my point of view are total liars, still believe they are ac=
tually good people, doing good, and that what is in their interests is good=
 for everyone in this world. They still believe that. They have a wonderful=
 insensitivity. They are unable to see themselves from another perspective.=
 Americans are very proud that this is the most mixed culture in the world,=
 but you only know the American version of otherness. You only know the Ame=
rican version of an Italian. You only know the American version of the Iris=
h people, of a Mexican, of a Spaniard or an Asian.

----- Original Message ----
From: Philip Sternberg <philip@eccentric.org>
To: Alex Laughlin-Dendy <aldendy@gmail.com>
Cc: Steve Osteen <sosteen@gmail.com>; sfraves@hyperreal.org
Sent: Thursday, August 31, 2006 4:01:22 PM
Subject: Re: [sfraves] NRR: Terrorists "drive taxi cabs in the daytime and =
kill at night"

The term "fascist" gets thrown around a lot, and often it's misapplied.

fas=E2=80=A7cism=E2=80=82 /=CB=88f=C3=A6=CA=83=C9=AAz=C9=99m/ - [fash-iz-uh=
m]
=E2=80=93noun
1.(sometimes initial capital letter) a governmental system led by a
dictator having complete power, forcibly suppressing opposition and
criticism, regimenting all industry, commerce, etc., and emphasizing
an aggressive nationalism and often racism.
2.(sometimes initial capital letter) the philosophy, principles, or
methods of fascism.

Terrorism is specifically when non-governmental groups attack civilian
concerns.  So in some sense terrorist and fascist are mutually
exclusive.  There's clearly a lot of gray area, (for instance, a
fascist state providing support to a terrorist organization, or a
group of terrorist who want to take over a government to impose
fascist rule) but blowing up passenger jets for the purpose of
instilling fear in the populace of another country is not really a
fascist act.

And on one of the other points--there are millions of non-arab muslims
in the world, both extremist and otherwise.

Philip

proper...
